## Melee
# Mishaps due to a Critical Failure on a Melee Attack

Roll a d100 to determine what happens when a melee attack results in a critical failure. 

1. You lose your grip on your weapon and it goes flying out of your hand.
2. You overextend and fall prone, leaving yourself open to attack.
3. Your weapon gets lodged in something nearby and you cannot retrieve it without an action.
4. You accidentally hit a nearby ally instead, dealing damage to them.
5. You slip in the heat of battle and your attack misses its target.
6. Your weapon gets tangled in your opponent's gear, and you need to spend an action untangling it.
7. The hilt of your weapon smacks you in the face, causing damage to yourself.
8. Your weapon gets stuck in the ground, and you need to spend an action to dislodge it.
9. You become dizzy from overexertion, and your attack misses its target.
10. Your weapon blade snaps off at the hilt.

...

100. Your weapon explodes in your hand, dealing damage to yourself and those nearby.

## Arcane
### d20 Mishaps due to a Critical Failure on an Arcane Attack

Roll a d20 when a critical failure occurs during an arcane attack to determine the resulting mishap:

1. You accidentally teleport yourself into the nearest solid object, suffering 2d10 force damage.
2. The spell rebounds off a magical ward, hitting a random ally within 30 feet of you.
3. Your attack hits an anti-magic field, causing all magic items within 30 feet to stop functioning for 1d4 rounds.
4. You open a portal to the Astral Plane, causing a random creature to be pulled through - roll on the "Random Astral Encounter Table".
5. A wild magic surge occurs, roll on the "Wild Magic Surge Table".
6. A nearby magical creature becomes hostile towards you for disrupting the magical weave.
7. Your spell accidentally hits an innocent bystander - roll on the "Innocent Bystander Table" to determine their fate.
8. You accidentally polymorph yourself into a small, harmless creature until the end of your next turn.
9. Your spell explodes in a burst, dealing half the damage to all creatures within 10 feet of you.
10. Your spell backfires, causing you to be stunned until the beginning of your next turn.
11. The spell fizzles out, wasting the spell slot without effect.
12. Your magical energy is drained, causing you to suffer one level of exhaustion.
13. You accidentally trigger a nearby glyph or magical trap - roll on the "Glyph/Trap Table" to determine the effect.
14. The spell causes a toxic reaction, dealing 1d6 poison damage to you each round for the next 1d4 rounds.
15. Your spell goes haywire, causing your vision to become blurry and your movement speed to be halved until the end of your next turn.
16. You summon a fiendish creature that is hostile towards you. It remains for 1d4 rounds or until it is defeated.
17. Your magic causes an earthquake, knocking prone all creatures within 10 feet of you.
18. You and a random ally within 30 feet of you switch places, potentially causing chaos.
19. Your spell deals damage to you instead of the target, suffering the full damage of the attack.
20. Your magic causes a surge of elemental power, roll on the "Elemental Surge Table" to determine the type and effect.
